    <h1 class='space-bottom1'>
      Mapbox GL JS
    </h1>

     <div class='quiet small space-bottom2'>Version: mapbox-gl.js {{site.version}}</div>

    <div class='prose space-bottom2'>
      <p>Mapbox GL JS is a JavaScript library that uses WebGL to render interactive maps from <a href='{{site.url}}/help/define-vector-tiles'>vector tiles</a> and <a href='{{site.url}}/mapbox-gl-style-spec'>Mapbox GL styles</a>.
      It is part of the <a href='https://github.com/mapbox/mapbox-gl'>Mapbox GL ecosystem</a> which includes <a href='{{site.url}}/mobile/'>Mapbox Mobile</a>, a compatible renderer written in C++ with bindings for desktop and mobile platforms.</p>

      <p>To get started, include the JavaScript and CSS files in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> of your HTML file.</p>
<div class='contain ' id='head-code'>
      {% highlight html %}
      <div class='pad2' >
<script src='{{site.tileApi}}/mapbox-gl-js/{{site.version}}/mapbox-gl.js'></script>
<link href='{{site.tileApi}}/mapbox-gl-js/{{site.version}}/mapbox-gl.css' rel='stylesheet' />
</div>{% endhighlight html %}
  <a class='icon clipboard pin-bottom space-bottom1 text-right quiet js-clipboard space-right1' href='#' data-clipboard-target='head-code'></a>
  </div>

      <p>Then include this code in the <code>&lt;body&gt;</code> of your HTML file to initialize a map on the page.</p>
      <div class='js-replace-token contain' id='body-code'>
{% capture getting_started_html %}
<div id='map' style='width: 400px; height: 300px;'></div>
<script>
var map = new mapboxgl.Map({
    container: 'map',
    style: 'mapbox://styles/mapbox/streets-v8'
});
</script>

{% endcapture %}
      <a class='quiet pin-bottom space-right1 text-right icon clipboard js-clipboard space-bottom1' href='#' data-clipboard-target='body-code'></a>

      {% highlight html %}{{ getting_started_html | insert_token }}{% endhighlight %}
    </div>
    </div>
